// `#import` is a region in the same family as `#module`/`#file`/`#foreign`. It supports a
// `{ ... }` block grouping several module names (and a bare `#import name` with the `;`
// now optional). Here a grouped import of two stdlib modules; the bare names they declare
// resolve (e.g. os's `arche_argc`).
// RUN: %arche check %s
#import {
  os term
}

main :: proc() {
  arche_argc()(n:);
  printf("argc=%d\n", n);
}
